  Locus:
    Page: 338
    Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Old Age
---
Nothing is inherently and invincibly young except spirit. And spirit can
enter a human being perhaps better in the quiet of old age and dwell there
more undisturbed than in the turmoil of adventure.
